To try out this example, just clone this repo, setup a database in the config/database.yml and run:

$ gem install gherkin cucumber-rails webrat database_cleaner
$ rake db:migrate
$ rake cucumber

I described the whole process in my blog:
http://alonsogarciapablo.com/blog/un-ejemplo-muy-sencillo-para-entender-el-desarrollo-dirigido-por-comportamiento-bdd-con-cucumber-y-ruby-on-rails/

Have fun!
